---
description: Terraform file structure and naming conventions for this project
alwaysApply: false
---

| main.tf | Module wiring — instantiate modules and pass variables |
| _variables.tf | Root input variables |
| _providers.tf | AWS provider config with default tags |
| _versions.tf | Terraform/provider version constraints and S3 backend |
| _locals.tf | Computed values and tag maps |
| _data.tf | Shared data sources |Prefix infrastructure files with _ to visually separate them from feature files.Module Directory LayoutEach module (e.g. teams-data/) follows:| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| _variables.tf | Module input variables |
| _output.tf | Module outputs |
| locals.tf | Derived names and identifiers |
| data.tf | Data sources (archives, IAM policy docs) |
| {feature}.tf | One file per feature/component (Lambda + IAM + triggers) |Naming ConventionsResources
- Use hyphens: aws_lambda_function.teams-data, aws_iam_role.daily-embedding-sync-role
- Pattern: {component}-{suffix} (e.g. teams-data-log-group)
Locals for Display NamesDerive all resource names from application_identifier in locals.tf:locals {
  application_identifier = var.application_identifier
  vector_bucket_name     = "${local.application_identifier}-knowledge-${var.account_id}"
  function_name          = "${local.application_identifier}-teams-data"
}
Variables
- snake_case for standard inputs (environment, region, account_id)
- PascalCase for external secrets/IDs (WebexCredentials, KnowledgeBaseId)
Environment Configurationterraform/config/
├── dev/
│   ├── variables.tfvars
│   └── backend.tfvars
├── test/
│   └── ...
└── prod/
    └── ...

- Init: terraform init -backend-config=config/{env}/backend.tfvars
- Plan: terraform plan -var-file=config/{env}/variables.tfvars
Backend
- S3 backend declared generically: backend "s3" {}
- Actual config in backend.tfvars per environment
- Bucket: cigna-tf-state-{account_id}, Key: {project}/{env}.tfstate
- DynamoDB lock table: cigna-tf-lock-{account_id}
TaggingDefault Tags (provider level)Corporate tags in _providers.tf: AssetOwner, CostCenter, ServiceNowBA, ServiceNowAS, SecurityReviewID, P2PResource Tags (locals)
- tags — standard resource tags passed to all resources
- data_tags — data classification tags for S3 (BusinessEntity, DataClassification, etc.)
ServiceNowAS is environment-dependent via ASbyEnv map.Resource Grouping
- Group related resources in a single file (Lambda + IAM role + policy + EventBridge trigger)
- Use comment headers for sections within a file: ##### EventBridge trigger #####
- Keep shared data sources in data.tf
Provider
- Default region: us-east-1
- Profile: saml
- CRR alias aws.crr for us-west-1 when cross-region replication is needed